  "text": "Successfully implemented a comprehensive hair color system using SVG data attributes. The system supports multiple color specification methods:\n\n1. **Default behavior**: `data-color=\"currentColor\"` uses body color (maintains existing behavior)\n2. **Contrast mode**: `data-color=\"contrast\"` chooses random color different from body\n3. **Color array**: `data-color='[\"#hex1\", \"#hex2\", ...]'` randomly selects from JSON array\n4. **Single color**: `data-color=\"#hex\"` uses specific hex color\n\n**Technical implementation**:\n- Updated `parse_defs()` function to extract `data-color` attribute\n- Modified agent generation to unpack the new color_spec parameter (had to update multiple tuple unpacking locations)\n- Added JSON parsing with error handling and fallback to body color\n- Implemented color selection logic with random choice from arrays\n\n**Emo hair configuration**: Used darker colors from palette: `[\"#A47E69\", \"#37759C\", \"#8C6BB1\", \"#9FA7A6\", \"#7CAB6A\", \"#F34B65\"]` to create more variety while maintaining the darker aesthetic.\n\nThe system is extensible - any hair asset can now specify its own coloring behavior using the same data attribute pattern.",
  "sections": [
    "Project Notes"
  ],
